HEADWORD: Amphigamous
<hw>Am*phig"a*mous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'amfi`</grk> + <?/ marriage.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having a
structure entirely cellular, and no distinct sexual organs; -- a term
applied by De Candolle to the lowest order of plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amphigean</ent>⟦br⟧
